<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   ROK's Use of National Security Law Criticized </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0403045994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0444 GMT 4 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0403045994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Sword-brandishing Cannot Be a Way Out" -- KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, March 4 (KCNA) -- The Kim Yong-sam puppet 
clique recently threw behind bars students of Chonnam National 
University and Choson University on the pretext that the 
Kwangju-South Cholla Provincial Federation of General Student 
Councils (Chongnyon) orchestrated a "violent demonstration" and 
"attempted to neutralize government power". 
  It also arrested students of Kyongbuk National University by 
invoking the "National Security Law", charging them with 
"posting an article sympathizing with the North's demand". 
  An analyst of NODONG SINMUN today says: The fact that the 
Kim Yong-sam group makes patriotic students a target of ruthless 
suppression shows that they are now seeking in a more 
undisguised way dependence on outside forces, not national 
independence, and North-South confrontation, not national unity, 
and fascist rule, not democracy. 
  Nowadays the Kim Yong-sam group is invoking the "National 
Security Law" quite often, charging students with connection 
with the North. This reveals once again its wicked intention to 
follow the road of confrontation with the North to its dying 
breath. 
  The puppets' grumble about "violent demonstrations" of 
students is a ridiculous jargon reminding one of a thief crying 
"stop thief!" Students have staged peaceful demonstrations 
urging the refusal of "parliamentary ratification" and 
renegotiation regarding the rice market opening, enraged at the 
Kim Yong-sam puppet clique's flunkeyist treachery in selling off 
the rice market. It is a duplication of the method employed by 
the military fascists of the "Fifth and Sixth Republics" to 
brand them as "rioters". 
  The Kim Yong-sam puppet clique's fascist suppression will 
result in digging its own grave. 

</TEXT>

