situation of the Korean peninsula to the brink of war. 
  The prevailing grave situation urges the South Korean people 
and students to turn out in the anti-war, anti-nuke struggle so 
as to remove the danger of war and defend the security of the 
nation. It is quite natural that they are vigorously waging 
this struggle. 
  The South Korean people and students will decisively crush 
the maneuverings of the U.S. imperialists and the Kim Yong-sam 
puppet clique to provoke a nuclear war by invigorating the 
