<H3> <TI>   Pamphlet on Reunification Issued in Sweden </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0403014794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 2214 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0403014794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 3 (KCNA) -- The publishing house of 
the Communist Party-KPML (R) [Communist Party of 
Marxist-Leninist Revolutionaries] of Sweden issued a booklet 
"Korea, a Divided Country". 
  In the preface the booklet notes that a fine socialist 
system 
has been established in North Korea, but fascist dictatorship is 
rampant in South Korea. 
  The preface says the South Korean authorities, with a view 
to 
keeping the country divided forever, built the largest ever 
concrete wall under the aegis of the United States and have 
ceaselessly staged provocative military exercises against North 
Korea. 
  Saying North Korea put forward a proposal for reunification 
through a confederacy based on one nation, one state, two 
systems and two governments, the preface stresses this proposal 
is the best way of achieving the reunification of the country. 

