<H3> <TI>   DPRK's Ho Chong To Return to Pyongyang </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0403003994 Seoul YONHAP in English 0031 GMT 4 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0403003994 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Washington, March 3 (YONHAP) -- Ho Chong, the chief 
North Korean representative at working-level contacts with the 
United States, will return to Pyongyang this weekend, officials 
at the North Korean mission to the United Nations said on 
Friday. Ho has been working as Pyongyang's deputy chief of 
mission to the world body. 
  A North Korean official disclosed the scheduled return of 
Ho, 
saying "he will return to Pyongyang this coming weekend, if 
there is no problem in reserving an airplane seat." Meanwhile, a 
source in Washington said Ho may be promoted to an assistant 
minister-level post for U.S. affairs due to his leading role in 
Pyongyang-Washington working-level contacts. 

</TEXT>

