<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reception of DPRK Broadcasts `Not Desirable' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0403003794 Seoul CHOSON ILBO in Korean 2 Mar 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> SK0403003794 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul CHOSON ILBO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Kim Min-pae] </F>
  [Text] Speaking on the cable television network system on 
28 February, Information Minister O In-hwan said that the 
government plans to allow the Christian Broadcast Network to 
begin broadcasting beginning next year and will issue additional 
permission to air culture, art, cartoon, and home-shopping 
programming. Minister O also revealed that "since North Korean 
broadcasting programs consists of only half of the truth and 
half is intended for instigation, reception of North Korean 
broadcasts by the domestic press and radio is not desirable." 
  Minister O said that the government plans to discontinue 
production of tht Taehan [Korea] news by the National Film 
Studio beginning next year, and will intensively review the plan 
for effective utilization of 102 staff workers now working in 
this studio. 

</TEXT>

