<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   PRC Asks ROK Support on UN Rights Resolution </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0403020594 Seoul CHOSON ILBO in Korean 4 Mar 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> SK0403020594 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul CHOSON ILBO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On 3 March, Chinese Ambassador to the ROK Zhang 
Tingyan visited the Foreign Ministry and met with Vice Foreign 
Minister Hong Sun-yong. Ambassador Zhang asked Vice Foreign 
Minister Hong to support the Chinese side's position when the UN 
Human Rights Committee in Geneva puts to a vote the "resolution 
for calling for the promotion of human rights in China" slated 
for 8 March. Vice Foreign Minister Hong stressed that "human 
rights are a dignified value which should not be infringed upon 
under any pretext," and revealed a position "to prudently review 
the issue by taking into account special relations between the 
ROK and the PRC." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

