<F P=100> Brunei, Malaysia &amp; Singapore </F>
<F P=101> Malaysia </F>
<H3> <TI>   SRV's Do Muoi To Pay Official Visit 24-28 Mar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0403102594 Kuala Lumpur BERNAMA in English 0338 GMT 4 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0403102594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur BERNAMA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kuala Lumpur, March 4 (OANA-BERNAMA) -- Vietnamese 
Communist Party's Secretary-General Do Muoi will make a four-day 
official visit to Malaysia from March 24, acccording to the 
Foreign Ministry here. It said in a statement issued here 
Thursday that the visit is at the invitation of Prime Minister 
Dr. Mahathir Mohamed. 
  While here, he will hold talks with Dr. Mahathir on 
bilateral 
relations and current regional and international issues. Do Muoi 
will make a visit to the southern state of Melaka where he will 
call on the governor, Syed Ahmad Shahabuddin. 

</TEXT>

