<H3> <TI>   Envoy Urges UN To Ensure Palestinian Safety </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0403082994 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 0000 GMT 4 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0403082994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Indonesian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Indonesia has asked the UN Security Council to pay 
serious attention and not neglect its responsibility in 
Israeli-occupied Palestine territory following the recent 
massacre of more than 50 Palestinians. (Isa Slamet Sudarga), 
deputy permanent representative to the United Nations, said 
Indonesia hopes the Security Council will not only end such 
atrocities against the Palestinians, but also make efforts to 
find a peaceful and comprehensive solution to the Middle East 
conflict. 
  Therefore, along with Palestine, Indonesia called on the 
Security Council to take concrete actions to ensure that Israel 
performs its duty to protect Palestinian citizens in accordance 
with the Geneva Convention. Indonesia also fully supported the 
resolution adopted by the Organization of Islamic Conference 
which called on the UN Security Council to discuss the massacre 
so as to end the Israeli oppression and safeguard the safety of 
Palestinians through the presence of international observers. 

</TEXT>

