<H3> <TI>   Army Official Denies KR Use Thai Territory </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0403054194 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in Thai 0000 GMT 
4 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0403054194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Thai </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Lieutenant Colonel Somkhuan Saenphattharanet, 
deputy spokesman of the Royal Thai Army, met with reporters over 
the Sieng Lapresse--spokesman of the Information Ministry of the 
Phnom Penh government, Cambodia--interview with AP. Lapresse 
said that Khmer Rouge [KR] forces delivered logs to Thailand for 
sale to earn money for use in their fight against the Cambodian 
Government and they also use Thai territory as a base for their 
operations. 
  Lt.Col. Somkhuan said such a statement is groundless and 
affects the image of Thailand. If one considers the issue 
thoughtfully, it is obvious that the present Thai Government has 
a clear policy to maintain good relations with Cambodia. One 
indication is the visit to Cambodia and Phnom Penh by Prime 
Minister Chuan Likphai in January this year. Another indication 
is that the Thai Government has provided Cambodia with 
assistance for rehabilitating the country in various fields. 
These are factors that assure very well the sincerity of 
Thailand. All this is because the Thai Government wishes to see 
peace established as soon as poosible in this region and if 
fighting continues in Cambodia, Thailand will suffer also. 

</TEXT>

