<F P=102> BK0403090494 Hanoi VNA in English 1741 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0403090494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA Mar 3 -- Singaporean Prime Minister Goh 
Chok Tong who is here for an official friendship visit to 
Vietnam paid a courtesy visit to party General Secretary Do Muoi 
this afternoon. 
  The prime minister affirmed the Singaporean Government's 
policy to continue accelerating the cooperation and exchange of 
experience with Vietnam, and to encourage Singaporean 
businessmen to further invest in Vietnam. 
  General secretary Do Muoi highly valued the Singaporean 
Government's assistance to Vietnam in personnel training and 
expressed his wish that the two countries will further promote 
their multifaceted cooperation, especially in the field of urban 
planning and management, tourism development and building of 
industrial zone and ship building and repairing technology. 
  Earlier in the day Deputy Prime Minister Phan Van Khai 
received Singaporean Minister of Trade and Industry Yeo Cheon 
Tong and minister in charge of finance and transport Teo Chea 
Hean. Foreign Minister Nguyen Manh Cam, for his part, received 
his singaporean counterpart. 
  The Singaporean delegation also met with Minister Do Quoc 
Sam, head of the State Planning Committee, Minister Dau Ngoc 
Xuan, chairman of the State Committee for Cooperation and 
Investment, and Minister of Trade Le Van Triet. 
  The two sides exchanged views on important issues in order 
to 
strengthen the friendship and mutual understanding, thus 
contributing to the acceleration of cooperation investment, and 
economic-trade exchanges between the two countries in the coming 
time. 
  The minister in charge of finance and transport witnessed 
the 
signing of documents on West Lake project of straits steamship 
land, an economic cooperation project between the two countries 
in Hanoi. 
  Some members of the delegation called at the construction 
site of the West Lake regency project, a joint venture between 
Lian Court group of Singapore and the Housing Investment and 
Development Company of Vietnam. 
  Also today, Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong and his wife paid a 
floral tribute to President Ho Chi Minh at his mausoleum. 

