<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Singaporean Prime Minister Meetings Reported </TI></H3>
<H4>   Goh Comments on SRV in ASEAN </H4>
<F P=102> BK0403093494 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
2300 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0403093494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Vietnamese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Italicized portions are recorded in English, fading into </F>
Vietnamese translation] 
  [Summary] Visiting Singapore Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong 
held a news conference in Hanoi on the evening of 3 March. At 
the conference, "Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong gave a briefing of 
the meetings with Vietnamese leaders at which both sides 
informed each other about the current situation of their 
country, exchanged views on issues necessary for promoting 
friendly relations and mutual understanding, and discussed 
economic, investment, and trade cooperation between Vietnam and 
Singapore in the period to come." 
  In response to a BANGKOK POST reporter's question regarding 
ASEAN membership for Vietnam, Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong said: 
  [Goh Chok Tong] Singapore supports Vietnam joining 
ASEAN, but it should be done at the appropriate time. When that 
will happen depends on how Vietnam can contribute to the 
activities and affairs of ASEAN. I suggest that Vietnam study 
these programs. Vietnam is presently an observer of ASEAN, and 
its membership in ASEAN is only a matter of time. ASEAN opens 
its door to Vietnam, and only Vietnam can decide when to 
join. 
  Answering a reporter of the Voice of Vietnam Radio who asked 
about the Vietnam-Singapore relations after the lifting of the 
U.S. trade embargo against Vietnam, he said: 
  [Goh Chok Tong] At the moment, Singapore is Vietnam's 
largest trading partner, and the eighth largest investor. With 
the lifting of the U.S. trade embargo, we believe more American 
investment will come to Vietnam, not immediately, but maybe in a 
few years. Relations between Vietnam and Singapore have a bright 
future, though they only started three years ago. It was a 
short time, but I can affirm that our relations are excellent. 
Vietnam has sent many missions to Singapore to study our 
experience. I believe that business relations between the 
United States and Vietnam will also develop very well. 
  Asked by a NHAN DAN reporter for his impression on his first 
visit to Vietnam, he said: 
  [Goh Chok Tong] The visit to Vietnam reminds me of 
Singapore 30 years ago. I believe that Vietnam has tremendous 
potential for economic development. Singapore's investment in 
Vietnam can only develop if Vietnam achieves political stability 
and economic development. I believe that in the coming period, 
Vietnam's economy will develop strongly. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

