<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA March 3 -- President Le Duc Anh today 
held talks with Mongolian President P. Ochirbat on a visit to 
Vietnam. 
  Speaking at the talks, President Le Duc Anh and President 
Ochirbat informed each other of the situation of each country, 
and exchanged views on measures aimed at developing the 
friendship and cooperation between Vietnam and Mongolia and the 
international and regional issues of common concern. 
  The two sides expressed their satisfaction at the 
consolidation and development of the traditional friendship and 
cooperation between the two countries and discussed measures to 
further promote these relations in the new situation. 
  The two sides agreed that an agreement on cooperation in 
economy, science and trade would be signed soon and will 
encourage and that the two sides would encourage and create 
favourable conditions for businessmen of the two countries to 
accelerate their co-operation in the forms of direct investment 
and joint venture. 
  Talking about international and regional issues, President 
Le 
Duc Anh and President Ochirbat paid much attention to the new 
steps of development in the Pacific-Asian region, and expressed 
their desire to broaden the friendly and cooperative relations 
of mutual benefit with the countries in the region aimed at 
building the Asian-Pacific region into a region of peace 
stability, friendship and cooperation in conformity with the 
aspiration and fundamental and lasting interests of the peoples 
in the region. 
  The Mongolian president invited President Le Duc Anh to 
visit Mongolia. President Anh accepted the invitation with 
pleasure. 
  The talks took place in an atmosphere of friendship and 
mutual understanding. 

</TEXT>

