<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Center for Japanese Study Established in Hanoi </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0403153494 Hanoi VNA in English 1501 GMT 4 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0403153494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA March 4 -- The Centre for Japan Study 
made its first public appearance here yesterday. 
  Present at the ceremony were Prof. Dr. Nguyen Duy Quy, 
member of the Communist Party of Vietnam Central Committee, and 
director of the National Centre for Social Science and 
Humanities, Hiroyuki Yushita, Japanese ambassador, and others. 
The Centre for Japan Study, under the National Centre for 
Social Science and Humanities, will conduct studies on Japan's 
history, economy, socio-polititics, culture and language with a 
view to providing scientific basis for the state to make 
domestic and foreign policies. The centre's establishment 
marked a new step of development in the relations between 
Vietnam and Japan. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-5192 </DOCNO>
