<H3> <TI>   Minister Opposes Sending Troops to Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0403063694 Melbourne Radio Australia in English 0500 GMT 4 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0403063694 </F>
<F P=104>  Melbourne Radio Australia </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Summary From Poor Reception] The United States has 
ignored an appeal by two United Nations officials in Bosnia for 
the deployment there of additional troops. Yashushi Akashi, a UN 
representative in Bosnia, also joined the debate on sending 
10,000 more troops to Bosnia. Australian Defense Minister 
Robert Ray says he opposed sending troops to Bosnia. Ray said 
the government requires certain conditions to be met before it 
can consider sending any soldiers. 

</TEXT>

