<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Premier Urges North To Take `Sincere Attitude' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0503053294 Seoul YONHAP in English 0528 GMT 5 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0503053294 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seongnam, Kyonggi Province, March 5 (YONHAP) -- 
Prime Minister Yi Hoe-chang urged North Korea on Saturday to 
achieve nuclear transparency and remove all obstacles to peace 
and unification of the Korean peninsula. Yi conveyed the 
message while speaking at the commencement ceremony for the 
reserve officers' training corps held at the students' Central 
Military School in Seongnam, a satellite city on the outskirts 
of Seoul. 
  He said, "North Korea should solve the common problems of 
South and North Korea by showing a more sincere attitude." 
  The North is delaying progress in inter-Korean talks 
intentionally, asking for things having nothing to do with the 
heart of the talks at a recent working-level contact on 
exchanging special envoys, Yi said. 
  "In order to win the unlimited competition in the world, all 
Koreans should concentrate on strengthening the nation's 
international competitiveness. For this, it is most important 
for the military to keep a water-tight national security 
posture." 

</TEXT>

