<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   N-S `Processing-on-Commission' Trade Increases </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0603084794 Seoul KYONGHYANG SINMUN in Korean 6 Mar 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> SK0603084794 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KYONGHYANG SINMUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] While inter-Korean trade is picking up this year, 
inter-Korean processing-on-commission trade [witak kagong muyok] 
has amounted to $2.78 million in the first two months of this 
year, recording 63 percent of the 1993 yearly total of this mode 
of trade. 
  According to the "Trend of Inter-Korean Trade in February" 
released by the National Unification Board on 5 March, the 
processing-on-commission trade during January-February period 
this year consisted of 160,707 men's jackets, 172,996 pairs of 
men's trousers, and 200,000 suit-covers on an approval basis, 
accounting for 63 percent of the total processing-on-commission 
trade amount of $4.38 million last year. However, the approval 
amount of inter-Korean trade during the same period was $24 
million, registering only a two percent growth over last year. 
  The businesses engaged in processing-on-commission trade are 
12 companies including Daewoo, Lucky-Gold Star, Samsung, and 
Kolon. 

</TEXT>

