<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official: Law Cannot Be Abolished </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0703033694 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 0310 GMT 7 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK0703033694 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A high-ranking Chongwadae [presidential office] 
official today revealed there is no change in the government's 
existing position that the National Security Law cannot be 
abolished, as there was no significant change in the situation. 
  This official said that some people hold that the Security 
Law should be abolished and the pertinent articles be absorbed 
into criminal law. However, the criminal law stipulates that the 
act of espionage must be committed between nations. Therefore, 
the article in the Security Law that defines North Korea as an 
antistate organization, not as a state, cannot be absorbed into 
the criminal law. 

</TEXT>

