<F P=102>  SK0503010594 Seoul YONHAP in English 2346 GMT 4 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0503010594 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, March 5 (YONHAP) -- The supreme public 
prosecutor summoned the chairman of the National Agricultural 
Cooperatives Federation (NACF), Han Ho-son, Friday night and 
questioned him overnight about allegedly embezzling part of a 
300 million won slush fund he had set aside from the budget for 
an NACF branch. 
  The prosecutor's office is expected to seek an arrest 
warrant 
for Han, 58, Saturday after further questioning him on the 
alleged misappropriation of the slush fund, its exact amount and 
its use. 
  Officials at the prosecutor's office said Han built up the 
slush fund by misappropriating NACF budgets set for local 
branches between April 1991 and October 1992. The officials 
said their investigation showed that the fund amounted to 300 
million won, of which Han allegedly embezzled 180 million won. 

