<F P=100> Indonesia </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Suharto Meets Bosnian Prime Minister </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0503101494 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 0700 GMT 5 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0503101494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Indonesian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Muslim Government of Bosnia-Herzegovina hopes 
that more members of the Nonaligned Movement [NAM] will support 
Bosnia-Herzegovina in its struggle against Serbian and Croatian 
aggressors. Bosnian Prime Minister Haris Silajdzic expressed 
this hope before reporters after calling on President Suharto in 
Jakarta. He was accompanied by Foreign Minister Ali Alatas 
during the meeting. The Bosnian prime minister briefed the NAM 
chairman on the latest situation in Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
According to Haris Silajdzic, Bosnia-Herzegovina hopes that the 
NAM members will continue to extend diplomatic support to 
Bosnia-Herzegovina in the United Nations. Bosnia-Herzegovina is 
also hoping for humanitarian aid from the international 
community. 
  The Bosnian guest, who arrived in Jakarta yesterday, today 
received an assistance fund from the National Committee for 
Solidarity with Bosnia-Herzegovina. The fund was handed over by 
Probosutejo, the committee chairman. 

</TEXT>

