<F P=100> Indonesia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Alatas, Silajdzic Hold Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0403161294 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 1500 GMT 4 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0403161294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Indonesian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bosnian Prime Minister Haris Silajdzic appreciates 
the spirit of Indonesian volunteers who are ready to go to 
Bosnia. He says, however, that Bosnia needs Indonesia's 
diplomatic and political support more urgently. Speaking to 
reporters after holding talks with Foreign Minister Ali Alatas 
in Jakarta this afternoon, Haris Silajdzic said he deeply 
appreciated the spirit of the volunteers. According to 
Silajdzic, the spirit of the volunteers is important because it 
reminds the Bosnians that they are not fighting alone. Bosnia, 
however, more urgently needs the diplomatic and political 
support of Indonesia as chairman of the Nonaligned Movement. 
According to the prime minister, the Indonesian volunteers will 
find it difficult to enter Bosnia because the country is in a 
critical condition. 

</TEXT>

