<H3> <TI>   Chea Sim Delegation Visit, Meetings Reported </TI></H3>
<H4>   Saman Vi-gnaket Meets Chea Sim </H4>
<F P=102> BK0503143494 Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network in 
Lao 1200 GMT 5 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0503143494 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Lao </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] This afternoon at the National Assembly Hall in 
Vientiane, His Excellency [H.E.] Saman Vi-gnaket, chairman of 
the National Assembly of the Lao People's Democratic Republic 
[LPDR], held a meeting with Samdech Chea Sim, chairman of the 
National Assembly of the Kingdom of Cambodia. 
  The Lao delegation attending this meeting included H.E. 
Khambou Sounisai, deputy chairman of the National Assembly, H.E. 
Dr. Khamliang Phonsena, chief of the Commission for Foreign 
Affairs of the National Assembly, and other members of the 
National Assembly. 
  The Cambodian national assembly delegation included H.E. 
(Chan Ven), chairman of the Interior, National Defense, 
Investigation, and Suppression Commission; H.E. Pen Thol, vice 
chairman of the Foreign Affairs, International Cooperation, 
Information, and Press Commission, and 12 other members. 
  The meeting lasted two hours with an atmosphere of intimacy 
and good understanding from start to finish. 
  After that, at 1100 the National Assembly delegation of the 
Kingdom of Cambodia led by Samdech Chia Sim paid a courtesy call 
on H.E. Khamtai Siphandon, prime minister of the LPDR. 
  This evening at the National Assembly Hall, H.E. Saman 
Vi-gnaket, chairman of the LPDR National Assembly, will host a 
reception dinner in honor of visiting Samdech Chia Sim, National 
Assembly chairman of the Kingdom of Cambodia and his party. 

</TEXT>

