<F P=100> Laos </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chea Sim Delegation Visit, Meetings Reported </TI></H3>
<H4>   PASASON Welcomes Delegation </H4>
<F P=102> BK0603112794 Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network in 
Lao 0000 GMT 5 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0603112794 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Lao </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [PASASON 5 March Editorial: "Wholeheartedly Welcome for a </F>
High-Level Delegation of the National Assembly of the Kingdom of 
Cambodia"] 
  [Text] In response to the invitation of His Excellency 
Saman Vi-gnaket, chairman of the National Assembly of the Lao 
People's Democratic Republic [LPDR], Samdech Chea Sim, chairman 
of the National Assembly of the Kingdom of Cambodia, and his 
delegation will begin an official friendship visit to the LPDR 
from the morning of 5 March. 
  Regarding this important and meaningful event in the 
Lao-Cambodia relations, the people of Vientiane and all the 
multiethnic Lao people throughout the country are very pleased 
and overwhelmingly joyous. They also feel highly honored to 
have an opportunity to welcome the high-level delegation of the 
National Assembly of the Kingdom of Cambodia. This official 
friendship visit to the LPDR by Samdech Chea Sim and his 
delegation occurs after the high-level delegations of the 
Government of the Kingdom of Cambodia and the Government of the 
LPDR [words indistinct]. This shows that the relations and 
cooperation in various fields between the LPDR and the Kingdom 
of Cambodia in the new era are developing significantly, 
especially between the governments and the legislative 
institutions of the two countries. The party, state, and 
multiethnic people of Laos have always closely followed 
developments in the Kingdom of Cambodia, regarding it as our 
close neighbor. We all realize that Cambodia is a nation of 
energetic and courageous traditions. During the period of the 
Khmer Kingdom a world wonder was erected -- the internationally 
famous Angkor Wat. Despite hardships in the course of history, 
due to the determination of internal factions coupled with 
international support, the Cambodian people have now entered a 
period of national construction and national reconcililation. 
At present this process has reached another step. With the 
said responsible determination of various factions, the 
fraternal Cambodian people in the Kingdom of Cambodia under the 
leadership of His Majesty King Norodom Sihanouk Voraman will 
convincingly succeed in making the Kingdom of Cambodia a kingdom 
of independence, peace, and neutrality. Together they will 
bring progress and prosperity to their country and develop 
friendly relations with other countries, beginning with their 
neighbors. 
  The traditional relations of friendship, solidarity, and 
cooperation between Lao and Cambodian peoples, have existed for 
quite a long time since the ancient days. They have been passed 
along from generation to generation from our ancestors. The Lao 
people have always firmly nourished such relations and still 
have honest and unchangeable intentions to continuously improve 
the existing good relations and make them flourish steadily. 
Nowadays, Lao and Cambodian peoples are attentively 
implementing the principles of the joint communique issued in 
July 1993 and the joint statement signed by the two governments 
in November 1993 of an agreement on economic, scientific, 
technological, and cultural cooperation between the two 
countries. The main purpose is to serve the interests of the 
peoples of Laos and Cambodia who share many similarities, such 
as cultural, traditional, and religious aspects. Suffice it to 
say the two countries deservingly enjoy their brotherly and 
neighborly relations and solidarity. 
  On this glorious occasion, all Lao people wish the people in 
Cambodia to attain a greater new victory and make a new life to 
further create national conciliation and build up the Kingdom of 
Cambodia under the monarchic leadership of King Norodom Sihanouk 
Voraman with everlasting progress and prosperity. We wish the 
visit to the LPDR by Samdech Chea Sim and his delegation 
glorious success. We are all confident that through the visit to 
the LPDR by the high-level delegation of the National Assembly 
of the Kingdom of Cambodia, the relations between the 
legislative institutions of the LPDR and the Kingdom of Cambodia 
will develop into a new stage that corresponds with economic, 
social, and cultural development of each country. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

