<F P=100> Laos </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Meets German Counterpart </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0503112194 Vientiane KPL in English 0922 GMT 5 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0503112194 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane KPL </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vientiane, March 5 (KPL) -- German Foreign Minister 
Klaus Kinkel, on March 3, met in Bonn his Lao counterpart 
Somsavat Lengsavat and exchanged views with him mainly on 
bilateral economic relations, reports Xinhua. 
  According to the Deutsche Presse-Agentur (DPA), during the 
talks, Kinkel spoke highly of the open economic policy of Laos, 
and said Germany will continue to offer aid to help Laos' 
development. 
  As for investment, Kinkel stressed that Laos itself must 
create overall conditions for it. Germany has provided 
development aid totalling some 80 million deutsche marks (about 
4.72 million U.S. Dollars) to Laos since 1990. 
  Somsavat Lengsavat is the first Lao foreign minister to 
visit 
Germany since the establishment of diplomatic relations between 
the two countries in 1958. 

</TEXT>

