<F P=100> NORTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   LDP's Kono Urges Hosokawa To Hand Over Power </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0703010194 Tokyo KYODO in English 0029 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0703010194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Embargoed by KYODO until "approximately" 0400 GMT] </F>
  [Text] Tokyo, March 7 KYODO -- Liberal Democratic Party 
(LDP) President Yohei Kono urged Prime Minister Morihiro 
Hosokawa on Monday to hand over power, saying the 
seven-month-old coalition government has completed its mission. 
  Kono, speaking at the start of a three-day interpellation 
session at the Diet, said the Hosokawa Cabinet has piled up 
policy errors. 
  The leader of the main opposition party criticized Hosokawa 
for carrying over compilation of the fiscal 1994 budget to this 
year, revoking a "national welfare tax" plan, failing to reach 
agreement in trade framework talks with the United States and 
giving up a cabinet reshaping plan. 
  "The Hosokawa Cabinet has now finished its mission," he 
said. 
  Kono accused Hosokawa of failing to maintain a consistent 
basic political stance following changes in the balance of power 
in the seven-party coalition. 
  Kono said the Japanese people are concerned that the 
country's future may go in an unfavorable direction under 
threats from a behind-the-scenes strongman. He did not identify 
the man but was apparently alluding to chief coalition 
strategist Ichiro Ozawa. 
  The breakdown in the February summit between Hosokawa and 
U.S. President Bill Clinton led to the reinstatement of the 
"Super 301" trade provision that gives the U.S. Government broad 
powers to impose sanctions, he said. 
  Representatives of political parties are scheduled to speak 
Monday through Wednesday in response to Friday's policy speeches 
by Hosokawa and three cabinet ministers. 
  Komeito's Nobuaki Futami and the LDP's Koji Kakizawa will 
speak after Kono at Monday's plenary session of the House of 
Representatives. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-5291 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas044_a_94017" </HT>


