<F P=100> NORTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Confidence Among Smaller Firms Reportedly Slumps </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0303085294 Tokyo KYODO in English 0709 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0303085294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, March 3 KYODO -- Confidence in the economy 
among Japan's small and medium-sized businesses slumped in 
February for the 40th straight month, Shoko Chukin Bank said 
Thursday [3 March]. The bank's survey of 800 companies produced 
an index reading of 43.9, up a tiny 0.4 point from January but 
staying below 50, the dividing line between an improvement or a 
decline in confidence. 
  Although it was the second month of modest improvement in 
still-depressed sentiment, the survey shows that the pace toward 
recovery continues to drag, said the bank, a quasigovernmental 
institution geared toward smaller firms. 
  Sales fell 4.3 percent last month from a year earlier, 
widening from the previous February's 2.5 percent year-on-year 
sales slump, according to the survey, taken in mid-February. 
  More companies continued to say sales prices were falling 
and 
to predict another fall in March. As a result, companies 
reporting worsening profitability and financing continued to 
predominate. 
  The survey's profitability index, measuring the percentage 
citing improvement minus that saying things are worsening, was a 
minus 12.1, slightly better than the minus 12.5 percent of 
January, with a minus 9.3 forecast for March. 
  The financing index was minus 5.9, slipping from January's 
minus 5.8, with a March forecast of minus 5.0. 
  Companies continued to report stock and employment excesses. 
The product inventory index, in which a minus reading indicates 
a surplus, worsened to minus 13.6 from minus 12.2, with a March 
forecast of minus 10.0. The employment index improved to minus 
4.0 from minus 5.9, with a March forecast of minus 3.9. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-5299 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas044_a_94025" </HT>


<HEADER>
