<F P=100> NORTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Lead, Zinc Industry Designated `Slump-Hit' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0403013494 Tokyo KYODO in English 0048 GMT 4 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0403013494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, March 4 KYODO -- The government decided on 
Friday [4 March] to designate the lead and zinc mining and 
smelting industry as a recession-hit industry eligible for 
government subsidies from March 9, 1994 until June 30, 1995. 
  The industry is now in serious recession as a result of 
reduced demand from the automobile and steel industries and the 
yen's appreciation. 
  When a certain industry is designated as a specific 
slump-hit 
enterprise, businesses in the industry will be given subsidies, 
to help them take steps to prevent unemployment and help workers 
laid off find new employment. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

