<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mongolian Leader Visit Continues, Meetings Noted </TI></H3>
<H4>   Ochirbat Visits Ho Chi Minh Mausoleum </H4>
<F P=102> BK0503143294 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
1430 GMT 4 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0503143294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Vietnamese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On the morning of 4 March, Mongolian President 
Punsalmaagiyn Ochirbat, his wife, and other distinguished 
Mongolian guests now on a visit to Vietnam laid a wreath paying 
tribute to President Ho Chi Minh at his mausoleum. The wreath 
carries the following inscription: A respectful Tribute to 
President Ho Chi Minh -- Glorious Man of the Vietnamese Nation. 
  The delegation also visited President Ho Chi Minh's 
residence 
and office. At Uncle Ho's stilt house, President Ochirbat posed 
for a while before some memorabilia that conjured up the image 
of the great leader of the Vietnamese people. He was apparently 
moved when Mr. Tran Viet Hoan, director of the late president's 
heritage complex, recalled a statement by President Ho Chi Minh 
that, although living far apart, the Vietnamese people and the 
Mongolian people love each other dearly and they have always 
supported each other. I firmly believe that the friendly and 
cooperative relations between the two countries will certainly 
develop with every passing day, thus contributing to the 
maintenance of peace in Asia and the world. 
  President Ochirbat entered his thoughts in a souvenir book 
and signed it. 
  After leaving Uncle Ho's stilt house, President Ochirbat and 
his wife visited the Ho Chi Minh Museum where he was welcomed by 
Curator Cu Van Truoc and the museum staff and was guided by them 
on a tour of various galleries. 

</TEXT>

