<H3> <TI>   Singapore's Prime Minister Ends Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0603150294 Hanoi VNA in English 1412 GMT 6 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0603150294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA March 6 -- Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong of 
Singapore and his party left Ho Hi Minh City this afternoon, 
ending their official visit to Vietnam. While in Ho Hi Minh 
City, Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong was received by Mayor Trung 
Tan Sang, who gave him a brief account of the development of the 
city and of the investment and business environment in the city. 
On March 4 the mayor of Ho Chi Mind City gave a banquet in 
honour of Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong and his party. On March 
5 the prime minister and other Singapore guests visited Saigon 
harbor and attended the ground breaking ceremony for the Ba 
Son-Keppel shipyard, a joint venture between Vietnam and 
Singapore. Meanwhile the minister of trade and industry, Yeo 
Cheow Tong, and the business delegation accompanying Singapore 
prime minister attended the launching of the Singapore- built 
handphone system. The Singaporean guests were seen off at Tan 
Son Nhat Airport by Deputy Chairman of the Ho Chi Minh City 
People's Committee Phan Chanh Truc and other senior Vietnamese 
officials. 

