officially announced that the two sides, in conformity with the 
agreement, have agreed on the suspension of the Team Spirit 1994 
joint military exercise. 
  The South Korean Defense Ministry announced on 3 March that 
it will discontinue the Team Spirit 1994 joint military exercise. 
  On the same day, a spokesman for the U.S. State Department 
also announced that the United States has agreed with South 
Korea's decision to cancel the 1994 Team Spirit joint military 
exercise. 

