<H3> <TI>   Paper Views Preconditions for Inspections </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0703050794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0459 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0703050794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 7 (KCNA) -- If the United States 
lays obstacle to the complete implementation of the agreement 
reached at the DPRK-USA contact in New York and create 
artificial difficulties in the way of the talks by bringing 
forward such a precondition as the exchange of special envoys 
between the North and South of Korea in the future, it will 
reveal its intention not to resolve the nuclear issue on the 
Korean peninsula, stresses NODONG SINMUN in a signed commentary 
Monday. 
  At a time when the agreed conclusions of the DPRK-USA 
contact 
in New York have begun to be implemented, the United States 
intends to set the exchange of special envoys between the North 
and South of Korea and the inspection by the IAEA [International 
Atomic Energy Agency] as preconditions of the suspension of the 
"Team Spirit 94" joint manoeuvres and the opening of the third 
round of the DPRK-USA talks, the analyst says, and continues: 
This makes us doubt whether it has the willingness to fully 
implement the conclusions or not. 
  The stand of the United States that it will take an action 
only when the other side acts first, shows that it seeks a 
solution to the issue from the position of strength. This will 
only bring difficulties to the solution of the issue. 
  Whether the issue is solved or not depends on how sincerely 
the United States, a dialogue partner, work to implement its 
commitments. 
  Of importance here is for the United States to strictly 
observe the principle of the joint statement between the DPRK 
and the United States and renounce the attitude and stand to set 
preconditions, persisting only in its assertions. Such attitude 
and stand are only harmful to the solution of the nuclear issue 
on the Korean peninsula. 
  The United States must show in deeds its sincerity and 
willingness to solve the issue as a partner of the dialogue. 

</TEXT>

