<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to the South Korean Munhwa Broadcast 
Network, U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher confirmed 
that the demand on the abolition of South Korea's National 
Security Law [NSL] is a U.S. official position -- not that of an 
individual person. In response to a question, he clarified that 
the United States will advice [chongyong] South Korea to repeal 
the NSL, even though it is a touchy issue. He added that the 
reason for such a U.S. demand is the possibility that the law 
might be abused. 
  The final confirmation by the U.S. secretary of state came 
after the puppet Foreign Ministry's announcement that Deputy 
Assistant Secretary of State Hubbard's comment was his own 
personal view, not a U.S. official position. 

