<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spokesman on Japan's Remarks on Nuclear Issue </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0703052194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0513 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0703052194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["DPRK Foreign Ministry Spokesman Denounces Japanese </F>
Reactionaries' Row Over `Nuclear Problem'" -- KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, March 7 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the 
DPRK Foreign Ministry answered a question of KCNA today 
concerning the spiteful hullabaloo of the Japanese authorities 
over the "nuclear issue" of the DPRK. 
  He told KCNA: 
  The third round of DPRK-U.S. talks is to open before long as 
a series of controversial matters between the DPRK and the 
United States including the "nuclear issue" have been 
coordinated. Japanese politicians including the high-level 
authorities, however, are slandering the DPRK, urging it to 
accept "special inspection." They seek in this to instigate the 
hardline conservatives of the United States to lay obstacles in 
the way of the DPRK-U.S. talks and attain their sinister 
political and military purposes. 
  We cannot but watch with vigilance the attempt of the 
high-placed officials of Japan to impede the settlement of the 
"nuclear issue" with rash acts against the DPRK and find a 
pretext for a lawful promotion of their nuclear armament, which 
has reached the danger line. 
  If Japan arms itself with nuclear weapons, the 
denuclearization of Northeast Asia cannot be realised, the 
inter-Korean joint declaration on denuclearization will be 
invalid and the denuclearization of the Korean peninsula will be 
virtually meaningless. 
  If Northeast Asia including the Korean peninsula is to be 
nuclear-free, not only Asia but also the world must pay due 
attention to Japan which is accelerating nuclear armament. 
  The denuclearization of Northeast Asia should lead to the 
total abolition of nuclear weapons worldwide. 

</TEXT>

