<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   KCNA Urges Japan To Give Up `Nuclear Design' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0703104194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1031 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0703104194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Japan Must Give Up Nuclear Design" -- KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, March 7 (KCNA) -- As plutonium fully 
enough for Monju, a fast breeder reactor built in Tsuruga city, 
Fukui Prefecture, has been transported, it will shortly be put 
into operation, NHK reported recently. 
  This is part of Japan's undisguised intention to produce 
nuclear weapons any time by securing large quantities of 
plutonium by itself, and thus become a nuclear power. 
  The annual capacity of Japan's reprocessing factories is 800 
tons, largest in the world. Japan has reportedly stockpiled 26 
tons of plutonium and will secure 100 tons by 2010. This amount 
is enough to make far more than 10,000 nuclear bombs. 
  Japan, which has already been possessed of electronic 
destructive device and other devices and technology of nuclear 
bombs, developed in February this year even long-range, large 
roket H-2 which can be used as inter-continental ballistic 
missile. 
  The facts show that Japan's nuclear armament has reached a 
danger line. 
  With the nuclear armament being accelerated in real earnest 
in Japan, a neighbour of the Korean peninsula, we cannot but 
cope with such a situation with vigilance. 
  The accelerated nuclear armament of Japan throws a snag in 
the way of the denuclearization of the Korean peninsula. 
  The Japanese reactionaries must give up their criminal 
nuclear design, clearly mindful of the grave consequences to be 
entailed by their moves to turn Japan into a nuclear power. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

