Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 6 (KCNA) -- A son of Jihad al-Araj, 
third secretary of the Palestinian embassy here, was born at the 
Pyongyang maternity hospital on February 16. 
  Mr. and Mrs. Araj wrote a letter to the dear leader Comrade 
Kim Chong-il, asking him to give a name to their second child 
born at the Pyongyang maternity hospital. 
  Upon receiving the letter, Comrade Kim Chong-il named the 
baby "Solmae," wishing him to grow in good health with a strong 
will and principle unyielding to any adversity. 
  A ceremony took place at the Palestinian embassy Saturday to 
convey the loving care of Comrade Kim Chong-il for Solmae. 
  A souvenir sent by Comrade Kim Chong-il was handed to the 
parents of Solmae amid a loud applause of the participants. 
  Addressing the ceremony, the Palestinian ambassador 
expressed 
heartfelt thanks to his excellency the dear leader Kim Chong-il, 
who had once named a Palestinian girl "Jindallae," for naming 
the baby Solmae this time. 
  The father of Solmae spoke next. 
  Noting that his excellency Kim Chong-il with extraordinary 
leadership ability gave a name to his son, he said this greatly 
encourages the fighting Palestinian people. He vowed to fight 
with strong will and braveness for the victory of the common 
cause of Palestine and Korea. 
  He said he would bring up Solmae to be strong as wished by 
his excellency the dear leader Kim Chong-il. 
  He asked a Korean official concerned to convey a gift 
carrying his family's best wishes for longevity to his 
excellency Kim Chong- il. 

</TEXT>

