<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kim Chong-il Attends Army Song, Dance Show </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0603132294 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1108 GMT 6 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK0603132294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1108 GMT 6 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Comrade Kim Chong-il, supreme commander of the 
Korean People's Army [KPA], watched the overall song and dance 
performance by the artists of the KPA entertainment group. 
  Comrade Kim Chong-il, chairman of the DPRK National Defense 
Commission and supreme commander of the KPA, watched the overall 
song and dance performance by the artists of the KPA 
entertainment group on 5 March. 
  Comrade Kye Ung-tae, member of the Political Bureau of the 
Workers Party of Korea [WPK] Central Committee and secretary of 
the party Central Committee; Comrades Kim Chung-nin, Kim Ki-nam, 
Kim Kuk-tae, and Kim Yong-sun, secretaries of the party Central 
Committee; and responsible functionaries of the party Central 
Committee and the field of press and publication were on hand. 
  The performance began with the orchestral music and chorus 
of 
"The Sound of Horses Hooves at Mt. Paektu." Various 
performances were presented such as the dance, "The Palanquin 
Carriage Is Running," and "The Final Showdown;" a mixed vocal 
duet, "Love of Officers and Men Which Is Blossoming Along the 
Marching Road;" a men's chorus, "We Will Deeply Bear in Our 
Hearts the Red Certification of the Party;" and a solo and 
kayagum [a Korean instrument with 12 strings] ensemble, "It Is a 
Paradise of Hope at Which the Whole World Is Looking." 
  In May 1992, the creators and artists of the KPA 
entertainment group highly upheld the militant task presented by 
the supreme comrade commander and brought about a new turning 
point in the artistic creation work. Therefore, they were able 
to present on stage magnificent artistic works that greatly 
contribute to indoctrinating the people and soldiers of the 
People's Army in a revolutionary way. 
  After watching the performance, Supreme Commander Comrade 
Kim 
Chong-il expressed great satisfaction over the fact that the 
creators and artists of the entertainment group were able to 
create and perform revolutionary and militant art works which 
are of high ideological and artistic spirit. He highly assessed 
their results, and gave them a thank-you message of the party 
Central Military Commission and the KPA supreme commander. 
  The Supreme Commander Comrade Kim Chong-il said that all 
performances that were put on stage are very good works that are 
in accordance with the character of the military and in 
conformity with the demand of the era. He pointed out that the 
performance by the entertainment group is giving great faith and 
courage to our people and soldiers of the People's Army due to 
its militant spirit and strong appeal. 
  The Supreme Commander Comrade Kim Chong-il said all art 
works including songs and dances well reflected the courage, 
wisdom, and revolutionary spirit of our People's Army, which is 
the party's army, a revolutionary army armored to uphold the 
party and the leader, defend socialism, and complete the 
socialist cause. He showed his satisfaction that the People's 
Army entertainment group has created many revolutionary and 
combat-oriented art works and successfully fulfilled its 
fundamental duty of indoctrinating the soldiers of the People's 
Army to devotedly serve for the party and the leader, and for 
the fatherland and the people with the self-consciousness of 
defenders of the party and revolution. 
  The Supreme Commander Comrade Kim Chong-il said the KPA 
entertainment group, a combat art unit of our revolutionary 
armed forces, should continue its effort in artistic activities 
for the revolutionary and combat indoctrination for the soldiers 
and concretely set forth creative directions to serve as the 
guidelines for artistic creative works. The Supreme Commander 
Comrade Kim Chong-il said it is important that the People's Army 
entertainment group well reflects in the art works the great 
political and ideological aspects and invincible might of the 
soldiers of the People's Army, who are strongly guaranteeing our 
party's revolutionary cause with armed forces firmly united 
around the party and the leader. 
  The Supreme Commander Comrade Kim Chong-il said to vividly 
show the soldiers' life, as did in the show, is a very important 
question in creative works and pointed out that the 
entertainment group should well describe the lofty spiritual 
world of the soldiers of the People's Army and how they 
struggle, including their loyalty toward the party and the 
leader, their spirit of devotion to serve the fatherland and the 
people, indomitable revolutionary spirit, and revolutionary 
comradely love. 
  The Supreme Commander Comrade Kim Chong-il pointed out that 
the People's Army entertainment group should keep its identity 
of being socialist, revolutionary, winning, grand, and 
magnificent not only in the contents but also in the format in 
conformity with its mission and duty as an art group which 
indoctrinates and serves the soldiers of the People's Army. 
  The Supreme Commander Comrade Kim Chong-il pointed out that 
as all art works created by the People's Army entertainment 
group should be perfect ideologically and artistically as they 
contribute to the indoctrination of the invincible revolutionary 
rank, a-match-for-a-hundred revolutionary fighters, and added 
that new orchestral music should be created in chuche-oriented 
and national format in conformity with the characteristics of 
the Army units. 
  The Supreme Commander Comrade Kim Chong-il said he firmly 
believes that the creators and artists of the People's Army 
entertainment group will actively contribute to our party's 
revolutionary cause by vigorously carrying out creative artistic 
activities that contribute to the indoctrination of the soldiers. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

