<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kim Chong-il's Economic Propaganda Work Noted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0703110894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1018 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0703110894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Vitality of Our Party's Policy of Economic Propaganda and </F>
Agitation" -- KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, March 7 (KCNA) -- NODONG SINMUN on March 
6 dedicated an article to the 20th anniversary of the 
publication of the famous work of the dear leader Comrade Kim 
Chong-il "On Vigorously Conducting Economic Propaganda and 
Agitation" on March 7, 1974. 
  Recalling that Comrade Kim Chong-il in this work indicated a 
unique line of vigorously conducting economic propaganda and 
agitation on the basis of a scientific analysis of the realistic 
demand of socialist economic construction in our country and 
precious practical experience, the author of the article says: 
  The great vitality of our party's policy of economic 
propaganda and agitation lies, first of all, in that it has 
brought home to the party members and working people our party's 
chuche-based line of economic construction and economic policy 
and guided them to thoroughly defend and implement them. 
  The work contains the idea of energetically conducting the 
work of arming the party members and working masses with the 
party's line of building an independent national economy and its 
economic policy in each period. 
  The proud reality in which all people have turned out and 
are 
achieving new miracles and feats, upholding the revolutionary 
economic strategy setpforth by our party, is a precious fruition 
of the arming of the party members and working masses with the 
party's line of economic construction and economic policy. 
  The great vitality of our party's economic propaganda and 
agitation lies in that with the brisk progress of economic 
agitation, the revolutionary zeal and the creative ingenuity of 
the masses have been brought into full play in socialist 
economic construction. 
  The dear leader in the work indicated concrete tasks arising 
in vigorously conducting economic agitation on the basis of the 
success and experience already attained. What is important here 
is to concentrate economic agitation on the fulfilment of 
economic tasks set forth by the party and the leader in each 
time. 
  The great effect of economic agitation was demonstrated by 
the completion of such difficult and gigantic project as the 
West Sea barrage in a short time and construction of many 
monumental edifices including the May Day Stadium in a brief 
period. 
  With stress laid on enlisting the idea of people in economic 
agitation, a change has taken place in the work of remoulding 
their idea [word indistinct] construction. 
  Noting that the great vitality of our party's policy of 
economic propaganda and agitation also lies in the successful 
application of the anti-Japanese guerrilla-style propaganda and 
agitation, the article says: This is a most revolutionary one 
which makes it possible to stir the hearts of the masses by 
conducting agitprop activities with mobility any time, without 
formality and not restricted by place and condition. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

